headline: Resubmitted Paper

The student hangs on to this prized paper and sells it to the highest bidder at the end of the term; the buyer submits it to the same professor during the next term and receives a “B”.  The next school year, another student submits the same paper to the same instructor and receives a “B+”. Finally, yet another student submits the paper for a fourth time and receives an “A”; the grade is accompanied by a written comment from the professor: “I’ve read this paper four times now, and I like it better each time.”
